Defendant Marie Alice Hoaglan in court with attorney Alexis Ray Liggins.  Defendant Marie Alice Hoaglan in custody.  Lucy Kronforst appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Plea hearing proceeds. Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant sworn, examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  The Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon not to possess any firearms., and that she may not vote until her civil rights have been restored. 

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense counsel and defendant.  Additional statements by:  defendants mother, Ms. Patricia G.  The Court ordered the following:

The Court imposed one (1) year at the House of Correction, with Huber for work, and good time, consecutive to Waukesha County case 13CF1378.  Credit given for 22 days.  Court STAYED said sentence and placed defendant on probation for two years, concurrent to Waukesha County case 13CF1378.  

 * Court ordered defendant to provide a DNA sample if one was not previously ordered and on file.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
 - Undergo a mental health evaluation;
 - No controlled substances or alcohol;
 - Urine screens;
 - AODA assessment; treatment, if needed;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Job and vocational training;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - Pay the DNA surcharge, costs, disbursements and supervision fees.  Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant, which is non-dischargable in bankruptcy.

Filed,
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
Pretrial Incarceration Credit form.
